Silver Wheaton Corp. - Strategy, SWOT and Corporate Finance Report


                            Synopsis

Silver Wheaton Corp. - Strategy, SWOT and Corporate Finance Report, is a source of comprehensive company data and information. The report covers the company's structure, operation, SWOT analysis, product and service offerings and corporate actions, providing a 360˚ view of the company.

Summary

- Detailed information on Silver Wheaton Corp. required for business and competitor intelligence needs
- A study of the major internal and external factors affecting Silver Wheaton Corp. in the form of a SWOT analysis
- An in-depth view of the business model of Silver Wheaton Corp. including a breakdown and examination of key business segments
- Intelligence on Silver Wheaton Corp.'s mergers and acquisitions (MandA), strategic partnerships and alliances, capital raising, private equity transactions, and financial and legal advisors
- News about Silver Wheaton Corp., such as business expansion, restructuring, and contract wins
- Large number of easy-to-grasp charts and graphs that present important data and key trends

Reasons To Buy

- Gain understanding of  Silver Wheaton Corp. and the factors that influence its strategies.
- Track strategic initiatives of the company and latest corporate news and actions.
- Assess Silver Wheaton Corp. as a prospective partner, vendor or supplier.
- Support sales activities by understanding your customers' businesses better.
- Stay up to date on Silver Wheaton Corp.'s business structure, strategy and prospects.

Key Highlights

Silver Wheaton Corp. (Silver Wheaton) is a precious metals company in Canada. The company is involved in the acquisition, development, production and operation of gold and silver mines. The company has interests in 22 operating mines and seven development stage projects. Its silver and gold projects include San Dimas and Penasquito, Cozamin in Mexico; Yauliyacu, Antamina and Zinkgruvan in Peru; 777 and Sudbury and Minto in Canada; Zinkgruvan in Sweden; Salobo in Brazil; and others. Silver Wheaton’s portfolio includes gold and precious metal streams on Barrick’s Pascua-Lama project, Hudbay’s Constancia project, and Vale’s Salobo and Sudbury mines. The company acquires silver and gold production from the counter parties located in Mexico, the US, Canada, Greece, Sweden, Peru, Chile, Argentina, and Portugal. Silver Wheaton is headquartered in Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada.

                            













